@{
    ViewBag.Title = "About";
}

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-8">
        <h1>About OrchardLite CMS</h1>
        
        <p class="lead">OrchardLite CMS is a scaled-down content management system inspired by the popular Orchard CMS. It has been specifically designed to serve as a realistic legacy application for AWS migration workshops.</p>
        
        <h2>Technical Architecture</h2>
        <p>The application demonstrates common patterns found in enterprise web applications:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Database Layer:</strong> MySQL with complex relational schema including foreign keys, indexes, and JSON data types</li>
            <li><strong>Application Layer:</strong> ASP.NET MVC with Entity Framework for data access</li>
            <li><strong>Presentation Layer:</strong> Responsive web interface using Bootstrap</li>
            <li><strong>Security:</strong> Role-based access control with audit logging</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Database Schema</h2>
        <p>The application includes a comprehensive database schema with 8 tables:</p>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Users</strong> - User accounts and authentication</li>
                    <li><strong>Roles</strong> - Role-based access control</li>
                    <li><strong>UserRoles</strong> - Many-to-many relationships</li>
                    <li><strong>ContentItems</strong> - Pages and blog posts</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>ContentParts</strong> - Additional metadata (JSON)</li>
                    <li><strong>MediaItems</strong> - File uploads and media</li>
                    <li><strong>Settings</strong> - Application configuration</li>
                    <li><strong>AuditLogs</strong> - Activity tracking</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <h2>Migration Scenarios</h2>
        <p>This application is perfect for demonstrating:</p>
        
        <h3>AWS Database Migration Service (DMS)</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Homogeneous Migration:</strong> MySQL to Amazon RDS for MySQL</li>
            <li><strong>Heterogeneous Migration:</strong> MySQL to Amazon Aurora PostgreSQL</li>
            <li><strong>Continuous Replication:</strong> Ongoing data synchronization</li>
            <li><strong>Schema Conversion:</strong> Using AWS SCT for complex migrations</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>AWS Transform for .NET</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>.NET Framework to .NET 6+:</strong> Modern runtime migration</li>
            <li><strong>Containerization:</strong> Docker and Amazon ECS deployment</li>
            <li><strong>Cloud-Native Patterns:</strong> Microservices decomposition</li>
            <li><strong>Managed Services:</strong> RDS, ElastiCache, CloudFront integration</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Sample Data</h2>
        <p>The application includes comprehensive sample data:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>4 user accounts with different roles (Administrator, Editor, Author, Subscriber)</li>
            <li>5 content items including pages and blog posts</li>
            <li>3 media items with realistic file information</li>
            <li>System settings for application configuration</li>
            <li>Audit logs showing realistic user activity</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="alert alert-info mt-4">
            <h4>Workshop Ready</h4>
            <p class="mb-0">This application is ready to be used in AWS migration workshops to demonstrate real-world migration scenarios with a complex, realistic database schema.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
